      "message": "I know this isn\u0027t the QEMU way, but it might be cleaner and more understandable to avoid global variables access from multiple places by defining a type for the table and proper methods, as in:\n\n  struct TcgUserRamTable {\n     TcgUserRamSlotInfo* slots;\n  };\n\n  static TcgUserRamTable* tcg_user_ram_table_get(void) {\n    static TcgUserRamTable* s_table;\n    if (!s_table) {\n       TcgUserRamTable* table \u003d (TcgUserRamTable *)malloc(sizeof(*table));\n       memset(table, 0, sizeof(*table));\n       s_table \u003d table;\n    }\n    return s_table;\n  }\n\n  static TcgUserRamInfo* tcg_user_ram_table_find_first_free_slot(TvgUserRamTable* table) {\n     ...\n  }\n\n  static void tcg_user_ram_table_map(TcgUserRamTable* table, ...) {\n    ...\n  }\n\n  static void tcg_user_ram_table_unmap(TcgUserRamTable* table, ...) {\n    ...\n  }\n\nI\u0027m mentioning this because when I was working on QEMU, the \"global variables are accessed from any place\" coding-style drove me mad and resulted in lots of surprises (though there were a few instances where it is necessary, e.g. inside TCG).",
